year: 2026

repository-code: "https://github.com/PardoEdgar/snail-cardiac-activity"

license: "MIT"

abstract: >
  This repository provides a computational workflow for quantifying cardiac activity and locomotion 
  speed in the land snail Cornu aspersum using optocardiography and treadmill-based assays. 
  The approach combines pixel intensity analysis, automated tracking of locomotion speed using TrackMate, 
  and deep learning-based segmentation with StarDist 2D. The pipeline integrates signal processing 
  and heart rate variability (HRV) analysis in R aiming to understand the relationship between 
  physiological adjustments and experimentally induced behavioral states.

keywords:
  - optocardiography
  - heart rate variability
  - locomotion
  - TrackMate
  - StarDist
  - image analysis
  - gastropod physiology
  - Cornu aspersum
